docs.lead_paragraph: The St. Louis Repuolican has received a letter from Fort Laramie, dated June 22, portions of which are of sufficient interest to republish. The correspondent says: We made the trip from Fort Kearney here in two weeks, but have been detained here a day by the crowd of emigrants at the ferry over the Laramic-the bridge having been swept away by the late freshet.
